{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778983455814,"sessionID":"ses_1cc61f63cffe3JDoCmXU5s6B5T","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_PVoEzp7Bst90SKnaoIsQiLLi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md","offset":1,"limit":400},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: Obsoleted `GO:0045550 geranylgeranyl reductase activity` and replaced it with `GO:0102067 geranylgeranyl diphosphate reductase activity`.\n2: \n3: Changes made:\n4: \n5: - Renamed `GO:0045550` to `obsolete geranylgeranyl reductase activity`\n6: - Converted the definition to standard obsolete-term form by prefixing it with `OBSOLETE.` while preserving the original PMID provenance\n7: - Removed the active `is_a` assertion from the obsolete term\n8: - Added an obsoletion comment stating that the term is equivalent to `GO:0102067`\n9: - Added `replaced_by: GO:0102067`\n10: - Added `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31963\" xsd:anyURI`\n11: - Added `is_obsolete: true`\n12: \n13: Rationale:\n14: \n15: - The issue discussion established that the activity represented by `GO:0045550` is covered by `GO:0102067`, and the request in the latest comment was to complete the obsoletion.\n16: - The obsolete term now follows GO obsoletion conventions: no logical axioms or relationships remain, and provenance/history are retained.\n17: \n18: Validation:\n19: \n20: - Pre-validation: `make travis_build` passed before edits\n21: - Post-edit validation: `make travis_build` passed after the obsoletion\n22: \n23: Notes:\n24: \n25: - `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0045550` now shows a larger current annotation footprint than the original issue body summarized, but the ontology request here was a direct replacement obsoletion to `GO:0102067`, which is what was implemented.\n26: \n27: Checklist:\n28: \n29: - [x] PLAN: analyzed issue context and latest instruction to obsolete the term\n30: - [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated before edits\n31: - [x] TERM-SEARCH: inspected `GO:0045550` and `GO:0102067` in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n32: - [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: consulted relevant term design guidance; no new logical definition added\n33: - [x] EDITS: used checkout/checkin workflow via `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl`\n34: - [x] RELATIONSHIPS: removed active axioms from the obsolete term as required\n35: - [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: applied term obsoletion guidance\n36: - [x] METADATA: added issue tracker item for this obsoletion; no new-term metadata was needed\n37: - [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes\n38: - [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: preserved existing PMID provenance; no new references introduced\n\n(End of file - total 38 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Obsoleted `GO:0045550 geranylgeranyl reductase activity` and replaced it with `GO:0102067 geranylgeranyl diphosphate reductase activity`.\n\nChanges made:\n\n- Renamed `GO:0045550` to `obsolete geranylgeranyl reductase activity`\n- Converted the definition to standard obsolete-term form by prefixing it with `OBSOLETE.` while preserving the original PMID provenance\n- Removed the active `is_a` assertion from the obsolete term\n- Added an obsoletion comment stating that the term is equivalent to `GO:0102067`\n- Added `replaced_by: GO:0102067`\n- Added `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31963\" xsd:anyURI`\n- Added `is_obsolete: true`\n\nRationale:\n\n- The issue discussion established that the activity represented by `GO:0045550` is covered by `GO:0102067`, and the request in the latest comment was to complete the obsoletion.\n- The obsolete term now follows GO obsoletion conventions: no logical axioms or relationships remain, and provenance/history are retained.\n\nValidation:\n\n- Pre-validation: `make travis_build` passed before edits","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778983455770,"end":1778983455811}},"id":"prt_e33ad4c140011tNUdRN3Mh63cI","sessionID":"ses_1cc61f63cffe3JDoCmXU5s6B5T","messageID":"msg_e33ad2f15001ooboMDjEbAjB57"}}
